title: Grateful Dead Live at City Island on 1983-06-22
lineage: master cassette > cd > eac > flac; sony tc-we435 > philips cdr870 Tracked in CDwave, FLACd Flac Frontend level 8
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, CC Rider, Ramble On Rose, My Brother Esau-> Deal

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Weezer City Island.......this show followed two stellar and memorable Merriweather Shows. We got there early and were alarmed by the outward presence of law enforement both by land and by sea.....hung with Harry the Sound Man for a while before we drifted to the front (we be there berry early).  Oh my, not the boys at their best......oh no no....  But you get these and you take the good with the night...and there was plenty......Soc, Don....the bridge...hangin' with Harry...I wouldn't trade that for Thurman Munson and Juan Marichal in the same deal....no, no, no.  Where are these days, these days......
